This is a lovely little game, albeit flawed. The difficulty depends entirely on the initial positioning of the levels (some levels took me a good couple minutes and other just a few seconds). The greatest flaw, however, was showing the finished level for a good half second before exploding it and going to the next one. With the care put into level building it would have been lovely to have the possibility to have an "album mode", where every finished level can be panned around and zoomed into.
